Mexican Stocks: Bimbo, Femsa Shares Advance; Penoles Slips

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-06-02T15:11:46Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-02/mexican-stocks-bimbo-femsa-shares-advance-penoles-slips.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:48 a.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.4 percent to 35,278.27.  Consumer products companies: Mexico’s consumer confidence
index may climb to 90.1 in May from 89.7 in April, according to
the median forecast of eight economists in a Bloomberg survey.
The national statistics institute will report the figure
tomorrow.  Grupo Bimbo SAB (BIMBOA MM), the world’s largest bread
maker, climbed 0.9 percent to 26.90 pesos. Fomento Economico
Mexicano SAB (FEMSAUBD MM),  Latin America ’s largest Coca-Cola
bottler, added 1 percent to 72.76 pesos.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s second-
largest mining company, fell 1.6 percent to 433.98 pesos. Silver
futures for July delivery slipped as much as 3.3 percent to
$36.46 an ounce on the Comex in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
